four flies on grey velvet ( italian : 4 &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; di &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 1971 italian-french giallo film written and directed by dario argento , from a story by luigi cozzi ( who also served as assistant director ) . the film is the third in director argento 's " animal trilogy " , having been preceded by the bird with the crystal plumage ( 1970 ) and the cat o ' nine tails ( 1971 ) .